  "riddle": "1. Seek the application that opens doors to foreign tongues — how many languages can you learn through it?\n\n2. The number you uncovered conceals a secret within its factors. What do you get when you sum its distinct prime factors?\n\n3. Which indigenous tongue flourishes in the heart of South America? You must now discover the number of souls who speak it natively.\n\n4. A bustling street embodies the origins of a famed city. Count the original inhabitants who laid its foundations — how many were there in total?\n\n5. From the previous clue, tally the digits of that founding number. What total emerges from this sum?\n\n6. A delicacy of the Philippines offers sweet resistance against the heat. What are the main components that create this refreshing mixture?\n\n7. A purple treat crowned with a sweet twist awaits: what base ingredient is blended to form the creamy delight of this unique ice cream?\n\n8. The article detailing a historic district in Canada whispers coordinates to those who seek it. What are its geographical markers?\n\n9. Standing on the threshold of an iconic area, how high above sea level does this neighborhood rest?\n\n10. Count the resting places for weary travelers nearby. How many hotels lie in wait around this vibrant locale?\n\n11. With your previous findings, combine the elevation from clue 9 with the hotel count from clue 10. What total do you achieve?\n\n12. Among healthcare havens in the vicinity, how many hospitals can be found near this lively area?\n\n13. Looking northward, how many citizens call the land of maple leaves home?\n\n14. Now, weave together knowledge from clues 3, 4, and 12: take the population you found and subtract the number of hospitals. Use the result to showcase how that figure transforms, taking its absolute difference with 6500000 and finding the final remainder when divided by 10. What single digit do you arrive at?",
